@pkancir thanks for the insights. Couple of questions:

 - So throttles use -1 as a special signal for when rc is not connected? We can clamp motor command in the gazebo side to [0, 1] by setting [`cmd_max` and `cmd_min`](#!/osrf/gazebo_models/src/ca9a9779a93a40d2766c07421c32e131f4841ba0/zephyr_delta_wing_ardupilot_demo/delta_wing.sdf?at=zephyr_demos&fileviewer=file-view-default#delta_wing.sdf-138) to [0, 1] if the apm motor command is simply [0, 1] and only -1 when rc is not detected.
 - Does the throttle controller actually want to leverage reverse thrust during flight in some scenarios?
